1 B. 1. a. On and after September 1, 1998:
2 (1) any child-placing agency contracting with a
3 person for foster family home services or in any
4 manner for services for the care and supervision
5 of children shall also, prior to executing a
6 contract, complete:
7 (a) a foster parent eligibility assessment for
8 the foster care provider except as otherwise
9 provided by divisions (2) and (4) of this
10 subparagraph, and
11 (b) a national criminal history records search
12 based upon submission of fingerprints for
13 any adult residing in the foster family home
14 through the Department of Human Services
15 pursuant to the provisions of Section 1-7-
16 106 of Title 10A of the Oklahoma Statutes,
17 except as otherwise provided by divisions
18 (2) and (4) of this subparagraph,
19 (2) the child-placing agency may place a child
20 pending completion of the national criminal
21 history records search if the foster care
22 provider and every adult residing in the foster
23 family home has resided in this state for at
24
